{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2755168-f400-4b2e-9733-b086064e3eeb","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default runner switched to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `dotnet test` integration). In **4.x**, the VSTest adapter/bridge is **no longer included**, so `vstest.console.exe` can't discover tests at all.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended):\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n   This uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively—no VSTest needed.\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward. The new platform is faster and doesn't require the VSTest host process.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e2e9015-fea3-4707-a0a3-dbf159110f78","outputTokens":250,"requestId":"082F:1E21:70DDF09:7E17A76:69EAD854"},"id":"c36b8a4d-53b9-4e61-8377-f51be427dd34","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:41:32.147Z","parentId":"76cc7378-8c34-4131-9ae4-3e42499c43ed"}
